Smart device repair company Wefix has donated 2 drones to Shark Spotters. CAPE TOWN Drones will be utilised this summer season to increase the safety at Cape Town beaches.Smart device repair company Wefix has donated 2 drones to Shark Spotters.The organisation's Sarah Waries says the devices will initially be used only at Muizenberg and Fish Hoek beaches. We will use the drone to spot the sharks, lower it to see the species to see if it s a dangerous shark and to track its movements. Wefix CEO Alex Fourie has called it a 'match made in heaven'.